Message.MsgText: CWXMA0108E=CWXMA0108E: Edition "{0}" of application "{1}" failed to be deployed onto server "{2}" on node "{3}".
Message.Explanation: Error(s) occurred when the specified application edition was attempted to be deployed onto the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0080E=CWXMA0080E: The required cluster parameter or node and server parameters are not specified.
Message.Explanation: Either the cluster parameter or node and server parameters are not specified.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure either the cluster parameter or node and server parameters are specified.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0086E=CWXMA0086E: The server named "{0}" on the node named "{1}" is of type "{2}", which is not a server type supported by the application. The application is only supported by the following server types: "{3}".
Message.Explanation: The specified server is not a type of server that supports the application.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified server name is a valid type for the application.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0021E=CWXMA0021E: An application with name "{0}" already exists. Select a different name.
Message.Explanation: Application names must be unique.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a unique application name that is not already in existence.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0121I=CWXMA0121I: The application named "{0}" is started on server "{1}" on node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The specified application started successfully on the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0060E=CWXMA0060E: The file "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified file could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified file name is a valid name for an existing file.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0001E=CWXMA0001E: The middleware application named "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified middleware application name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified application name is a valid name for an existing middleware application.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0101E=CWXMA0101E: The application named "{0}" cannot be started because it is not deployed to any targets.
Message.Explanation: The specified application needs to be deployed to at least one deployment target before it can be started.
Message.UserResponse: Associate the application with the necessary deployment targets.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0007E=CWXMA0007E: The module named "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified module name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified module name is a valid name for an existing module.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0040E=CWXMA0040E: The value of context root is invalid. The context root must start with a "/" character.
Message.Explanation: The context root must start with a "/" character.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a context root that starts with a "/" character.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0107E=CWXMA0107E: The application named "{0}" does not exist on server "{1}" on node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The specified application is absent on the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the application is properly installed, check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0085E=CWXMA0085E: The server named "{0}" on the node named "{1}" is not a standalone server.
Message.Explanation: The specified server is not a standalone server.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified server name is a valid name for an existing standalone server.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0020E=CWXMA0020E: The edition named "{0}" already exists.
Message.Explanation: Edition names must be unique for an application.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a unique edition name that is not already in existence for the application.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0010E=CWXMA0010E: The module named "{0}" could not be found in the archive.
Message.Explanation: The specified module could not be located inside the application archive.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified module is a valid module in the archive.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0110E=CWXMA0110E: Edition "{0}" of application "{1}" does not exist on server "{2}" on node "{3}".
Message.Explanation: The specified application edition is absent on the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0006E=CWXMA0006E: The virtual host named "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified virtual host name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified virtual host name is a valid name for an existing virtual host.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0106E=CWXMA0106E: The application named "{0}" failed to be stopped on server "{1}" on node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: Error(s) occurred when the specified application was attempted to be stopped on the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0084E=CWXMA0084E: The edition parameter is required, as the application "{0}" has several editions.
Message.Explanation: The command requires the edition parameter for applications with several editions.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the edition parameter.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0005E=CWXMA0005E: The server named "{0}" could not be found on the node named "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The specified server name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified server name is a valid name for an existing server.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0105E=CWXMA0105E: The application named "{0}" failed to be started on server "{1}" on node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: Error(s) occurred when the specified application was attempted to be started on the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0083E=CWXMA0083E: The application "{0}" has no editions.
Message.Explanation: The application has no editions defined in the configuration repository.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the application has an edition defined in the configuration repository, or uninstall the application.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0089E=CWXMA0089E: The module named "{0}" is not specified.
Message.Explanation: The required module that is in the application archive is not specified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the module and the necessary configuration parameters.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0124I=CWXMA0124I: Edition "{0}" of application "{1}" has been undeployed from server "{2}" on node "{3}".
Message.Explanation: The specified application is undeployed successfully from the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0004E=CWXMA0004E: The node named "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified node name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified node name is a valid name for an existing node.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0104E=CWXMA0104E: The application named "{0}" failed to be stopped.
Message.Explanation: Error(s) might have occurred when the specified application was attempted to be stopped.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0082E=CWXMA0082E: The cluster parameter cannot be specified in conjuction with the node or server parameters.
Message.Explanation: The cluster parameter and node and server parameters are mutually exclusive parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure only the cluster parameter or node and server parameters are specified.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0088E=CWXMA0088E: The cluster named "{0}" is of type "{1}", which is not a cluster type supported by the application. The application is only supported by the following cluster types: "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster is not a type of cluster that supports the application.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified cluster name is a valid type for the application.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0123I=CWXMA0123I: Edition "{0}" of application "{1}" has been deployed onto server "{2}" on node "{3}".
Message.Explanation: The specified application is deployed successfully onto the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0062E=CWXMA0062E: The length of file "{0}" is zero.
Message.Explanation: The specified file is zero bytes in length.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a file with a length greater than zero bytes.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0003E=CWXMA0003E: The dynamic cluster named "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified dynamic cluster name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified cluster name is a valid name for an existing dynamic cluster.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0103E=CWXMA0103E: The application named "{0}" failed to be started.
Message.Explanation: Error(s) might have occurred when the specified application was attempted to be started.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0009E=CWXMA0009E: The script with type "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified script could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified script type is a valid type for an existing script.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0042E=CWXMA0042E: A validation error occurred in task {0}. Application name, {1}, is not valid. An application name cannot begin with a leading dot, cannot have leading or trailing spaces and cannot contain any of the following characters: / , # $ @ : ; " * ? < > | = + & % '' ]]
Message.Explanation: The specified application name contains an unacceptable character. An application name cannot begin with a leading dot, cannot contain leading or trailing spaces and cannot contain any of the following characters: backward slash (\), slash (/), number sign (#), dollar ($), at sign (@), colon (:), asterisk (*), question mark (?), quotation marks ("), greater than sign (>), less than sign (<), pipe (|), semicolon (;), or comma (,), equal sign (=), plus (+), percent (%), ampersand (&), single quotation mark (') square brackets (]]).
Message.UserResponse: Specify an application name that does not contain any of these unacceptable characters.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0109E=CWXMA0109E: Edition "{0}" of application "{1}" failed to be undeployed from server "{2}" on node "{3}".
Message.Explanation: Error(s) occurred when the specified application edition was attempted to be undeployed from the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server logs for details, resolve any issues, then retry.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0081E=CWXMA0081E: Both the node and server parameters must be specified.
Message.Explanation: The node and server parameters are mutually dependent parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure both the node and server parameters are specified.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0087E=CWXMA0087E: The application named "{0}" is of type "{1}". An application of type "{2}" is expected.
Message.Explanation: The specified application is not of the expected type.
Message.UserResponse: Specify an application of the expected type.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0022E=CWXMA0022E: The context root "{0}" already exists. Specify a different context root.
Message.Explanation: Context roots must be unique.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a unique context root that is not already in existence.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0122I=CWXMA0122I: The application named "{0}" is stopped on server "{1}" on node "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The specified application stopped successfully on the particular server.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0061E=CWXMA0061E: The file "{0}" has an invalid extension. Valid extensions for this file include: "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The specified file has an invalid extension.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified file name extension is valid.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0002E=CWXMA0002E: The edition named "{0}" could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified edition name could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specified edition name is a valid name for an existing edition.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0102E=CWXMA0102E: The application named "{0}" cannot be stopped because it is not deployed to any targets.
Message.Explanation: The specified application needs to be deployed to at least one deployment target before it can be stopped.
Message.UserResponse: Associate the application with the necessary deployment targets.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0008E=CWXMA0008E: The target server or dynamic cluster could not be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified target could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the specifed target is a valid target for an existing module.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0041E=CWXMA0041E: The value of context root is invalid. The context root cannot be only "/".
Message.Explanation: The context root cannot be only "/".
Message.UserResponse: Specify a context root that starts with "/" and follows by other alphanumeric characters.

Message.MsgText: CWXMA0090E=CWXMA0090E: The required moduleName parameter must be specified and cannot be empty.
Message.Explanation: The moduleName parameter must be specified and cannot be empty.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the moduleName parameter is specified and is not empty.
